parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to reduced vehicle safety and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent warning lights on the dashboard
and stop lights; beeping sounds; loss of ABS function; and potential brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: brake pedal sticking to the floor
delayed return of the brake pedal to its normal position
and sudden loss of brake pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Warning Lights and Beeping Sounds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent warning lights and beeping sounds can distract the driver and cause confusion, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent warning lights on the dashboard
and stop lights; beeping sounds; and potential loss of ABS function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and turbocharger problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
